e open-ended dynamics. While SLF4J normally loads classes statically, I wonder if the native implementation will need reflection metadata. It seems like Class.forName supports constant strings, but I’m concerned about whether tests generate enough metadata. If reachability metadata is empty, there may be some failures with reflection. We imported classes that might be internal, so I need to ensure we're adhering to guidelines about using public APIs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reducing SLF4J Logger Use**\\n\\nI’m considering how we can minimize direct usage of the Slf4jLogger and Slf4jLoggerFactory classes while ensuring we have the necessary testing bindings. It seems like I can still use the public StaticLoggerBinder. Since Slf4jLoggerFactory is also public, it looks like that could work fine for our needs. It’s good to know there's a path forward while respecting the guidelines about avoiding direct reflection or internal classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking log manager levels**\\n\\nI'm thinking there might be an issue with JBoss logmanager version 2.1.17, specifically around the `org.jboss.logmanager.Level.INFO`. I’m wondering if this version actually defines the levels INFO, WARN, and ERROR. It could be possible that in version 1.3, there were custom definitions for these levels. To clarify, I'll need to use `javap` to inspect the class and see what’s defined there. Let's take a closer look!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_aezgiF7bwFISkVGH0QSSTbaU|fc_0865110725f547ea0169f3dddda99c8194830b90aa6b9f1c86", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.3.0.Final/c1c333a1635fd27232bd1608facf9d5dc50b947f/jboss-logmanager-1.3.0.Final.jar -public org.jboss.logmanager.Level | sed -n '1,120p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4815, "output": 1445, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite"